[Cajititlan lake is 10 miles south of Guadalajara. The lake is 2 km wide by 9 km long, and a town of the same name sits on its northern side (for a picture, see http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/65/Cajititlan.jpg).

Pictures of the episode can be accessed at http://resources3.news.com.au/images/2014/09/02/1227044/477931-f73ed3b0-31fb-11e4-aafa-2c4cfd90ea1d.jpg; http://resources0.news.com.au/images/2014/09/02/1227044/480492-43142ab6-31fb-11e4-aafa-2c4cfd90ea1d.jpg; http://resources0.news.com.au/images/2014/09/02/1227044/477440-0ddb6ca0-31fc-11e4-aafa-2c4cfd90ea1d.jpg.

A ProMED-mail/HealthMap of the affected area can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/awFa. - Mod.PMB]
